{"title_page": "List of Escheators of Ulster", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of the Members of Parliament appointed as '''Escheator of Ulster''', a notional 'office of profit under the crown' which was used at times [[Resignation from the British House of Commons|to resign]] from the [[Irish House of Commons]].\n\nThe office was formerly substantive. It was founded in 1605, when the [[escheator]]ship for Ireland was divided among the provinces of [[Connaught]], [[Leinster]], [[Munster]], and [[Ulster]].{{sfn|Reports from committees|p=78}}\n\n==Substantive holders==\n* bef. 1760: John King{{sfn|Reports from committees|p=78}}\n\n==Members of the Irish House of Commons==\n* 1799: [[Luke Fox (politician)|Luke Fox]] ([[Clonmines (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Clonmines]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=691}}\n* 1799: [[Charles Ruxton]] ([[Ardee (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Ardee]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=689}}\n* 1799: [[Henry Stewart (politician)|Henry Stewart]] ([[Longford Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Longford Borough]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=689}}\n* 1799: [[George Sandford, 3rd Baron Mount Sandford|George Sandford]] ([[Roscommon Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Roscommon Borough]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=690}}\n* March 1799: [[Hugh Howard (1761\u20131840)|Hugh Howard]] ([[St Johnstown (County Donegal) (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|St Johnstown]]){{sfn|Beaven|1881|p=39}}\n* 1800: [[Theophilus Blakeney]] ([[Athenry (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Athenry]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=688}}\n* 1800: [[Sir Richard St George, 2nd Baronet]] ([[Athlone (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Athlone]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=691}}\n* 1800: [[Thomas Lindsay (1759\u20131811)|Thomas Lindsay]] ([[Castlebar (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Castlebar]]){{sfn|Beaven|1881|p=40}}{{sfn|Return of the names...|p=689}}\n* 1800: [[Henry Luttrell (wit)|Henry Luttrell]] ([[Clonmines (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Clonmines]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=691}}\n* 1800: [[William Thomas Monsell]] ([[Dingle (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Dingle]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=688}}\n* 1800: [[George Bunbury]] ([[Gowran (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Gowran]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=688}}\n* 1800: [[Robert Taylour (MP)|Robert Taylour]] ([[Kells (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Kells]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=690}}\n* 1800: [[Charles Silver Oliver]] ([[Kilmallock (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Kilmallock]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=689}}\n* 1800: [[Robert Alexander (politician)|Robert Alexander]] ([[Newtownards (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Newtownards]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=687}}\n* January 1800: [[Barry Boyle St Leger]] ([[Doneraile (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Doneraile]]){{sfn|Beaven|1881|p=39}}\n* February 1800: [[Robert Johnson (1745\u20131833)|Robert Johnson]] ([[Hillsborough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Hillsborough]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=687}}\n* April 1800: [[Sir Thomas Staples, 9th Baronet|Thomas Staples]] ([[Knocktopher (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Knocktopher]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=688}}\n* May 1800: [[Charles Vane, 3rd Marquess of Londonderry|Charles William Stewart]] ([[Thomastown (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Thomastown]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=688}}\n\n==Members of the United Kingdom House of Commons==\n* February 1801: [[William Talbot (1776\u20131851)|William Talbot]] ([[Kilkenny City (UK Parliament constituency)|Kilkenny City]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=213}}\n* March 1804: [[John Claudius Beresford]] ([[Dublin City (UK Parliament constituency)|Dublin City]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=227}}\n* February 1819: [[Richard Nevill (1743\u20131822)|Richard Nevill]] ([[Wexford Borough (UK Parliament constituency)|Wexford Borough]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=284}}\n\nIn 1838, all of the Irish escheatorships were abolished by the [[Lord Lieutenant of Ireland]].{{sfn|Reports from committees|p=79}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n*{{cite book | ref={{harvid|Reports from committees}} | title=Reports from committees | volume=12 | year=1894 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sagTAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA2-PA79}}\n*{{cite book | ref={{harvid|Return of the names...}} | title=Return of the names of every Member returned to serve in each Parliament | year=1879 | volume=Part II | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RWMUAAAAQAAJ}}\n*{{cite journal | last=Beaven | first=Arthur B. | journal=Collectanea Genealogica | title=Errors in the official return of the Members of the Irish House of Commons | year=1881 | pages=33\u201341 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2SgAAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA33}}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Escheator]]\n*[[Resignation from the British House of Commons]]\n\n[[Category:Lists of British people|Escheators of Connaught]]\n[[Category:Government of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Lists of Irish people]]\n[[Category:Lists of Irish parliamentarians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of the Members of Parliament appointed as '''Escheator of Ulster''', a notional 'office of profit under the crown' which was used at times [[Resignation from the British House of Commons|to resign]] from the [[Irish House of Commons]].\n\nThe office was formerly substantive. It was founded in 1605, when the [[escheator]]ship for Ireland was divided among the provinces of [[Connaught]], [[Leinster]], [[Munster]], and [[Ulster]].{{sfn|Reports from committees|p=78}}\n\n==Substantive holders==\n* bef. 1760: John King{{sfn|Reports from committees|p=78}}\n\n==Members of the Irish House of Commons==\n* 1799: [[Luke Fox (politician)|Luke Fox]] ([[Clonmines (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Clonmines]]){{sfn|Return of the names...|p=691}}\n* 1799: [[Charles Ruxton]] ([[Ardee (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Ard